Sentencas: Proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs) with BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY) electrolyte were fabricated by impregnating Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) into La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-delta-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (LSF-BZCY) composite cathode.
Titulo: La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ composite cathode enhanced by Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ impregnation for proton conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction analysis showed that SSC and LSF were chemically compatible, which verified the feasibility of SSC impregnation on the composite cathode.
Titulo: La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ composite cathode enhanced by Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ impregnation for proton conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The SEM results exhibited that evenly distributed SSC nano-particles formed on the cathode surface and the amount of nano-particles increased with elevated SSC loading value.
Titulo: La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ composite cathode enhanced by Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ impregnation for proton conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances of the symmetrical and single cells were substantially improved by virtue of SSC impregnation.
Titulo: La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ composite cathode enhanced by Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ impregnation for proton conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The long-term stability of impregnated single cell was also tested.
Titulo: La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ composite cathode enhanced by Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ impregnation for proton conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The loading amount of 15 wt.% SSC after impregnation was proved to be the optimal value in improving the overall performance of BZCY electrolyte H-SOFCs with LSF-BZCY composite cathode.
Titulo: La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ composite cathode enhanced by Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ impregnation for proton conducting SOFCs
